                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#1v">f. 1v</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning reconciliation.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>: የሽበቃ፡ ሃድጉ፡ ልጅ፡ ና፡ የኀይታና፡ ሐማር፡ ልጅ፡
                              ገደለች፡ ኛ፡ ሲታረቁ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in Amharic, during the time of šum ʾagame Kasa
                              (governor of ʾAgame in 1914-18, 1941-48), by Gabra Ḥǝywat (of) Mayraza
                              (probably May Raza Takla Hāymānot, THMR). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>: Prohibition to transgress the church’s property rights
                              (concerning the donation of fitawrari Ḫāyla Mikāʾel?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>: በ፲፱፻፲፩፡ ዓመተ፡ ምህረት፡ ዘወሐቦ፡ ፊታውራሪ፡ ሐይለ፡
                              ሚካኤል፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ጊዎርጊስ፡ ጎናይ፡…</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The note is written in the year of mercy 1911 (= 1918/19 A.D.) Pen
                              trial in the first two lines written in the same hand as the main
                              text; the prohibition note is added in a later hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#13r">f. 13r</locus>
                           <desc>: Donation note</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#13r">13r</locus>: ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘደጅ፡ አዝማች፡ ሰብአ፡ ጋዲስ፡ ዘወሀባ፡
                              ለቅዱስ፡ ጊዮርጊስ፡ ዘመነቦት፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሀ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ልዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡
                              አሜን።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the same hand as the name Za-Manfas Qǝddus in the
                              supplication formulas. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The word śäyṭan "devil" is written upside down, in the
                           main text, on <locus target="#14v">14v</locus>, 65v.&#xD; - The scribe
                           reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the end of the line on
                           many fols.: <locus target="#22r">22r</locus>, 25v, 27v, 68v.&#xD; - The
                           scribe used compressed script: <locus target="#65v">65v</locus>,
                           76v.&#xD; - Omitted letters and words are inserted interlineally or
                           written in the margin, in very small script: e.g., <locus target="#13v">13v</locus>, 16r, 25r, 59r, 63r, 89r, 109r.&#xD; - Corrections
                           written over erasures on many fols.: e.g., <locus target="#5r">5r</locus>, 10v, 17r, 60r, 73v, 83v.&#xD; - Erasures marked with thin
                           lines: <locus target="#12r">12r</locus>, 18r, 24r, 52v.&#xD; - Erasures
                           marked with frame: <locus target="#37r">37r</locus>, 38r, 38v.&#xD; -
                           Erasures: <locus target="#33r">33r</locus>, 34r, 79r, 88r, 99v.&#xD; -
                           Pen trials, scribbles and doodles: fols.: 1r, 2r, 2v, 31r, 36r, 44r, 44v,
                           56v, 75r, 83r.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><!--2019-04-02+02:00 Updated QGM-005 
            from DomLib -->
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Coloured (red) thread is inserted in the upper
                              corner of fols. 53, 95, 112.</desc>
                        </item>
